{
  "stem": "1799.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was able to procure extra food here and there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I know I ended up very often with more ration.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know I didn't steal it from others.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I was able to procure it, or people would give it to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Or maybe a German guard took a liking to me, knowing I was speaking German, and would maybe give it to me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were such people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it helped me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what happened, especially towards the end of the war, most of the inmates, most of the interned people, were from Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were either from Hungary, or from Poland, or from Russia, or from East Germany-- the eastern part of Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they did not speak German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They either spoke Yiddish, or they spoke Polish, or they spoke Russian or Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I spoke fluent German, so that guards hearing-- there were very few German Jews in the camps during the whole time that I was there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were definitely in the minority.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so when German guards or German staff heard German spoken by inmates, they, they somehow took note.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was an advantage to me, which sometimes worked in my favor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in that I was able to communicate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was able to understand what the German guards were saying.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was able to act as an interpreter at times, if the situation required it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was trying to just kind of act as a-- as a little bit of an intermediate to make matters more tolerable.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I say they did that, which they did, it was-- it didn't happen very often.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It didn't happen very often, but it contributed to my survival.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
